  "text": "Elsewhere, [CITATION_1] demonstrated that increases in brake onset time, such as those observed in our study, can increase the likelihood and severity of a rear-end collision. The fact that older adults were involved in fewer collisions can be attributed, at least in part, to the greater following distance and slower driving speed of this cohort.",
